(-48.65 / 2.302585) \u2248 10^(-21.13) \u2248 7.4 \u00d7 10^(-22).\n\nThus, \u03c1_c = 10\u207b\u00b2\u2079 / (7.4 \u00d7 10\u207b\u00b2\u00b2) = 10\u207b\u00b2\u2079 / 7.4 \u00d7 10\u207b\u00b2\u00b2 = (1 / 7.4) \u00d7 10\u207b\u2077 \u2248 0.1351 \u00d7 10\u207b\u2077 = 1.351 \u00d7 10\u207b\u2078 g/cm\u00b3.\n\nLet's verify with Equation (1):\n\n(\u03c1_\u2609 / \u03c1_c)^\u03b1 = (10 / 1.351 \u00d7 10\u207b\u2078)^0.09457 = (7.403 \u00d7 10\u2078)^0.09457.\n\nCompute ln(7.403 \u00d7 10\u2078) = ln(7.403) + 8 ln(10) \u2248 2.002 + 18.4207 = 20.4227.\n\nMultiply by \u03b1: 20.4227 * 0.09457 \u2248 1.932.\n\ne^1.932 \u2248 6.9, which is close to A = 6.907755. Good.\n\nLet's compute more precisely. Let's use \u03b1 = 0.09457, \u03c1_c = 1.351 \u00d7 10\u207b\u2078.\n\nCompute (10 / 1.351e-8) = 7.403e8.\n\n(7.403e8)^0.09457 = e^(0.09457 * ln(7.403e8)) = e^(0.09457 * 20.4227) = e^(1.932) \u2248 6.9, which is A = 6.907755. The slight difference is due to approximate \u03b1.\n\nLet's solve for \u03b1 more precisely. Let's set up the equation:\n\n(10\u00b3\u2070)^\u03b1 = A / B = 6.90775527898214 / 0.0100503358513792 = 687.300000 (exact value: let's compute it as 6.90775527898214 / 0.0100503358513792 = 687.300000... let's check with calculator: 0.0100503358513792 * 687.3 = 0.0100503358513792 * 600 = 6.03020151082752, 0.0100503358513792 * 87.3 = 0.877151082, total = 6.03020151082752 + 0.877151082 = 6.9073525928, which is very close to 6.90775527898, so the exact A/B is approximately 687.300000 (the difference is due to more precise calculation, but for practical purposes, 687.3 is fine).\n\nSo, \u03b1 = log(687.3) / log(10\u00b3\u2070) = ln(687.3) / (30 ln 10).\n\nCompute ln(687.3):\n\n687.3 = 6.873 \u00d7 10\u00b2, so ln(687.3) = ln(6.873) + 2 ln(10) \u2248 1.927 + 4.605 = 6.532.\n\nMore precisely, ln(687.3) = 6.532700 (using calculator).\n\n30 ln(10) = 30 * 2.302585093 = 69.07755279.\n\nThus, \u03b1 = 6.532700 / 69.07755279 \u2248 0.09457.\n\nNow, let's compute \u03c1_c using Equation (2):\n\n\u03c1_c = \u03c1_cosm / (B)^(1/\u03b1) = 10\u207b\u00b2\u2079 / (0.01005033585)^(1/0.09457).\n\nCompute (0.01005033585)^(1/0.09457):\n\nFirst, 1/0.09457 \u2248 10.574.\n\n0.01005033585 = 1.005033585 \u00d7 10\u207b\u00b2.\n\nSo, (1.005033585 \u00d7 10\u207b\u00b2)^10.574 = (1.005033585)^10.574 \u00d7 10^(-2\u00d710.574) = (1.005033585)^10.574 \u00d7 10^(-21.148).\n\nCompute (1.005033585)^10.574:\n\nUsing the approximation (1 + x)^n \u2248 e^(nx) for small x:\n\nx = 0.005033585, n = 10.574,\n\nnx = 0.005033585 * 10.574 \u2248 0.05323,\n\nso e^0.05323 \u2248 1.0547.\n\nThus, (1.005033585)^10.574 \u2248 1.0547.\n\n10^(-21.148) = 10^(-21) \u00d7 10^(-0.148) \u2248 10^(-21) \u00d7 0.711 \u2248 7.11 \u00d7 10^(-22).\n\nThus, (0.01005033585)^10.574 \u2248 1.0547 \u00d7 7.11 \u00d7 10^(-22) \u2248 7.5 \u00d7 10^(-22).\n\nTherefore, \u03c1_c \u2248 10\u207b\u00b2\u2079 / 7.5 \u00d7 10\u207b\u00b2\u00b2 = 1.333 \u00d7 10\u207b\u2078 g/cm\u00b3.\n\nLet's check with more precise calculation using logarithms:\n\nLet\u2019s compute (0.01005033585)^(1/\u03b1) where \u03b1 = 0.09457.\n\nTake natural log: (1/\u03b1) * ln(0.01005033585) = (1/0.09457) * (-4.59988) \u2248 10.574 * (-4.59988) \u2248 -48.65.\n\ne^(-48.65) = 10^(-48.65 / 2.302585) \u2248 10^(-21.13) \u2248 7.4 \u00d7 10^(-22).\n\nThus, \u03c1_c = 10\u207b\u00b2\u2079 / 7.4 \u00d7 10\u207b\u00b2\u00b2 = 1.351 \u00d7 10\u207b\u2078 g/cm\u00b3.\n\nNow, let's verify both conditions with these values.\n\nFirst, check R1: \u0398(10 g/cm\u00b3) = exp(-(10 / \u03c1_c)^\u03b1) = exp(-(10 / 1.351e-8)^0.09457).\n\nCompute 10 / 1.351e-8 = 7.403e8.\n\n(7.403e8)^0.09457 = e^(0.09457 * ln(7.403e8)) = e^(0.09457 * 20.4227) = e^(1.932) \u2248 6.9.\n\nThus, exp(-6.9) \u2248 10^(-3) (since ln(10^3) = 6.9078, so exp(-6.9078) = 10^(-3)). Perfect, that's exactly R1.\n\nNow, check R2: \u0398(10\u207b\u00b2\u2079 g/cm\u00b3) = exp(-(10\u207b\u00b2\u2079 / \u03c1_c)^\u03b1) = exp(-(10\u207b\u00b2\u2079 / 1.351e-8)^0.09457).\n\nCompute 10\u207b\u00b2\u2079 / 1.351e-8 = 10\u207b\u00b2\u00b9 / 1.351 \u2248 7.403e-22.\n\n(7.403e-22)^0.09457 = e^(0.09457 * ln(7.403e-22)) = e^(0.09457 * (ln(7.403) - 22 ln(10))) = e^(0.09457 * (2.002 - 50.656)) = e^(0.09457 * (-48.654)) = e^(-4.599) \u2248 0.01005.\n\nThus, exp(-0.01005) \u2248 0.99, which is R2.\n\nPerfect, both conditions are satisfied.\n\nNow, let's get the numerical values to 3 significant figures.\n\nFirst, \u03b1 \u2248 0.0946 (since 0.09457 rounds to 0.0946).\n\n\u03c1_c \u2248 1.35 \u00d7 10\u207b\u2078 g/cm\u00b3 (since 1.351 \u00d7 10\u207b\u2078 rounds to 1.35 \u00d7 10\u207b\u2078).\n\nWait, let's confirm with more precise calculation of \u03b1.\n\nLet's compute A/B exactly:\n\nA = 3 ln(10) = 3 * 2.302585093 = 6.907755279,\n\nB = -ln(0.99) = 0.01005033585,\n\nA/B = 6.907755279 / 0.01005033585 \u2248 687.300000 (exactly, let's compute it: 6.907755279 / 0.01005033585 = 687.300000...).\n\nNow, \u03b1 = ln(A/B) / ln(10\u00b3\u2070) = ln(687.3) / (30 ln 10).\n\nCompute ln(687.3):\n\nUsing calculator, ln(687.3) = 6.532700 (more precisely, 6.532700).\n\n30 ln 10 = 69.07755279.\n\nThus, \u03b1 = 6.532700 / 69.07755279 \u2248 0.09457, which is 0.0946 to 3 sig figs.\n\nNow, \u03c1_c:\n\nFrom Equation (2): (\u03c1_cosm / \u03c1_c)^\u03b1 = B \u21d2 \u03c1_c = \u03c1_cosm * (1/B)^(1/\u03b1).\n\n1/B = 1 / 0.01005033585 \u2248 99.50125.\n\n(99.50125)^(1/\u03b1) = (99.50125)^(10.574) (since 1/\u03b1 \u2248 10.574).\n\nCompute 99.50125 = 100 * 0.9950125,\n\nso (99.50125)^10.574 = (100)^10.574 * (0.9950125)^10.574 = 10^(21.148) * (0.9950125)^10.574.\n\n(0.9950125)^10.574 \u2248 e^(10.574 * ln(0.9950125)) \u2248 e^(10.574 * (-0.004996)) \u2248 e^(-0.0529) \u2248 0.9485.\n\nThus, (99.50125)^10.574 \u2248 10^21.148 * 0.9485 \u2248 10^21.148 * 0.9485.\n\n10^21.148 = 10^21 * 10^0.148 \u2248 10^21 * 1.406 \u2248 1.406 \u00d7 10^21.\n\nThus, (99.50125)^10.574 \u2248 1.406 \u00d7 10^21 * 0.9485 \u2248 1.333 \u00d7 10^21.\n\nTherefore, \u03c1_c = 10\u20