7 10\u207b\u2078 g/cm\u00b3.\n\nThe difference between 1.33 and 1.35 is due to the approximation in the logarithm. To get a more precise value, let's use the exact ratio.\n\nLet\u2019s define x = \u03c1_c.\n\nFrom R1: (10 / x)^\u03b1 = 3 ln 10,\n\nFrom R2: (10\u207b\u00b2\u2079 / x)^\u03b1 = -ln 0.99.\n\nLet\u2019s take the ratio of R1 to R2:\n\n(10 / 10\u207b\u00b2\u2079)^\u03b1 = (3 ln 10) / (-ln 0.99) \u21d2 (10\u00b3\u2070)^\u03b1 = (3 ln 10) / (-ln 0.99).\n\nCompute the right-hand side:\n\n3 ln 10 \u2248 6.907755,\n\n-ln 0.99 \u2248 0.01005034,\n\nso RHS = 6.907755 / 0.01005034 \u2248 687.300.\n\nThus, 10^(30 \u03b1) = 687.300.\n\nTaking log base 10: 30 \u03b1 = log10(687.300) \u2248 2.8372,\n\nso \u03b1 = 2.8372 / 30 \u2248 0.094573.\n\nNow, using R2 to find x:\n\n(10\u207b\u00b2\u2079 / x)^\u03b1 = 0.01005034,\n\nso 10\u207b\u00b2\u2079 / x = (0.01005034)^(1/\u03b1),\n\nx = 10\u207b\u00b2\u2079 / (0.01005034)^(1/\u03b1).\n\nCompute (0.01005034)^(1/0.094573) = (0.01005034)^10.573.\n\nAs before, ln(0.01005034) = -4.59988,\n\nso ln((0.01005034)^10.573) = 10.573 * (-4.59988) \u2248 -48.64,\n\nthus (0.01005034)^10.573 = e^(-48.64) \u2248 10^(-48.64 / 2.302585) \u2248 10^(-21.125) \u2248 7.5 \u00d7 10^(-22).\n\nThus, x = 10\u207b\u00b2\u2079 / 7.5 \u00d7 10\u207b\u00b2\u00b2 = 1.333 \u00d7 10\u207b\u2078 g/cm\u00b3.\n\nTo three significant figures, \u03b1 = 0.0946, \u03c1_c = 1.33 \u00d7 10\u207b\u2078 g/cm\u00b3.\n\nWait, let's check with \u03b1 = 0.094573:\n\nCompute (10\u00b3\u2070)^0.094573 = 10^(30 * 0.094573) = 10^2.83719 \u2248 687.3, which matches.\n\nNow, compute \u03c1_c using R1:\n\nx = 10 / (3 ln 10)^(1/\u03b1) = 10 / (6.907755)^(1/0.094573).\n\n6.907755^(1/0.094573) = 6.907755^10.573.\n\nln(6.907755) = 1.932,\n\nso 10.573 * 1.932 \u2248 20.42,\n\ne^20.42 \u2248 7.38 \u00d7 10^8,\n\nthus x = 10 / 7.38 \u00d7 10^8 \u2248 1.355 \u00d7 10\u207b\u2078.\n\nThe difference between 1.33 and 1.35 is due to the approximation in the logarithm calculation. To resolve this, let's use more precise values.\n\nLet's use the exact expression for \u03c1_c from R2:\n\n\u03c1_c = \u03c1_cosm * (B)^(-1/\u03b1) = 10\u207b\u00b2\u2079 * (0.01005033585)^(-1/\u03b1).\n\nWe have \u03b1 = ln(A/B) / ln(r) = ln(687.3) / ln(10\u00b3\u2070).\n\nLet\u2019s compute 1/\u03b1 = ln(10\u00b3\u2070) / ln(687.3) \u2248 69.07755 / 6.5327 \u2248 10.574.\n\nNow, (0.01005033585)^(-10.574) = (1/0.01005033585)^10.574 = (99.50125)^10.574.\n\nCompute 99.50125^10.574:\n\nLet\u2019s write 99.50125 = 100 * 0.9950125,\n\nso (100 * 0.9950125)^10.574 = 100^10.574 * 0.9950125^10.574 = 10^21.148 * (0.9950125)^10.574.\n\nCompute (0.9950125)^10.574:\n\nTake natural log: 10.574 * ln(0.9950125) = 10.574 * (-0.004996) \u2248 -0.0529,\n\nso (0.9950125)^10.574 \u2248 e^(-0.0529) \u2248 0.9485.\n\nThus, 10^21.148 * 0.9485 \u2248 10^21 * 10^0.148 * 0.9485 \u2248 10^21 * 1.406 * 0.9485 \u2248 10^21 * 1.333.\n\nThus, 99.50125^10.574 \u2248 1.333 \u00d7 10^21.\n\nTherefore, \u03c1_c = 10\u207b\u00b2\u2079 * 1.333 \u00d7 10^21 = 1.333 \u00d7 10\u207b\u2078 g/cm\u00b3.\n\nNow, let's check with R1:\n\n(10 / 1.333e-8)^0.094573 = (7.5e8)^0.094573.\n\n7.5e8 = 7.5 \u00d7 10^8,\n\nln(7.5e8) = ln(7.5) + 8 ln(10) \u2248 2.015 + 18.4207 = 20.4357,\n\n0.094573 * 20.4357 \u2248 1.931,\n\ne^1.931 \u2248 6.90,\n\nso exp(-6.90) \u2248 10^(-3), which matches R1.\n\nFor R2:\n\n(10\u207b\u00b2\u2079 / 1.333e-8)^0.094573 = (7.5e-22)^0.094573,\n\nln(7.5e-22) = ln(7.5) - 22 ln(10) \u2248 2.015 - 50.656 = -48.641,\n\n0.094573 * (-48.641) \u2248 -4.599,\n\ne^(-4.599) \u2248 0.01005,\n\nso exp(-0.01005) \u2248 0.99, which matches R2.\n\nThus, the values are consistent.\n\nTo three significant figures:\n\n\u03b1 \u2248 0.0946,\n\n\u03c1_c \u2248 1.33 \u00d7 10\u207b"
